ed</li> <li>A lot of pekko.util classes for Scala version compatibility have been removed</li> <li>Big change for all Java DSL users due to the removal of <code>pekko.japi.Function</code> (and related classes) to use <code>pekko.japi.function.Function</code> instead (lambdas should recompile ok but if you declared variables or functions explicitly, then you may need to change your imports)</li> <li>New pekko-serialization-jackson3. Users who are happy with the pekko-serialization-jackson, which uses Jackson 2, can stick with that</li> <li>Changed the pekko-serialization-jackson lz4-java dependency to <code>at.yawk.lz4:lz4-java</code>, a fork that has important bugfixes</li> </ul\nTERM dependency y, then you may need to change your imports)</li> <li>New pekko-serialization-jackson3. Users who are happy with the pekko-serialization-jackson, which uses Jackson 2, can stick with that</li> <li>Changed the pekko-serialization-jackson lz4-java dependency to <code>at.yawk.lz4:lz4-java</code>, a fork that has important bugfixes</li> </ul> <h3><a href=\"#upgrade-notes\" name=\"upgrade-notes\" class=\"anchor\"><span class=\"anchor-link\"></span></a>Upgrade notes</h3> <ul> <li>Agrona was updated from 1.x to 2.x, which <a href=\"https://github.com/aeron-io/agrona/wiki/Change-Log#200-2024-12-17\">means</a> you may have to add <code>--add-opens java.base/jdk.internal.misc=ALL-UNNAMED</code> if you use the Java Module System and Pekko Remote</li> </ul> </div> <div> <a href=\"https://github.com/apache/pekko/tree/v2.0.0-M1/docs/src/main/paradox/release-notes/releases-2.0.md\" title=\"Edit this page\" class=\"md-source-file md-edit\"> Edit this page </a> <\n\n--- https://pekko.apache.org/docs/pekko/2.0.0-M1/project/release-notes.html\nERR HTTP Error 404: Not Found\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1782626197010}}
[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating Scala compilation issues**\n\nI'm encountering an issue where a \"java run fails\" message is actually indicating that I need to compile Scala due to the removal of TypedActor. It seems I might require an extra Maven dependency, like pekko-testkit_2.13 for testing. Even though the existing tests didn’t use testkit, meaningful coverage can be achieved without it. There appears to be a need for additional dependencies, possibly including logging support, especially since I’m working with Java 21 or higher due to virtual threads.\n\n**Looking into virtual-thread support**\n\nI'm noticing that the library supports a virtual-thread dispatcher, but there doesn’t seem to be an environment property associated with it. I need to find evidence in the documentation to clarify this. I should search the migration docs for version 2.0 to see if there’s any mention of the removal of classic typed actors. This may give me the insights I need to understand the changes better. I'll get on this now!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0119555cb460abf9016a40b7884a788190ba57db77d766e490\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqQLeTPKfU6UXbMZvkCChe1F_5ti-DaXMVOKCoiTkXisp49dg9c87dFTzZBH2bMDsjm9qC70_5QVqoKaxd_JRNeJYjAokjMuq4qsKwmjKs0h4S7D06phqyZh3VhaAtwqTk6PUOw9WfMANoea1AK13_3aCbOchPT_4GNtCV1Zx7QKKoiN4y45Fwg3cYhq0mhi1CPeUU3P_c2GAlnRew32m78uXBVbBG3VRr2NK2KNRuP-74JV8-YAS9peIk4a7eCVrsF6bi2gRkch4heT3klyIQ9tx5zrXLSGYs88k1h06PRJlN_H1YP27e0JiKn-mRl7TUzFF-AAaSLixN2fl3rRiNrav8tWNj7gSSMOxHy1owRWX0KgyIcoSmQ5_Hwm45yBX7N84DWTzrWH-U2aTmjJEKSzRR8yXfMJ7qpvToNNGLwzC-Ht36Lf7pV47uctPr5SzxUXtqCvuDMZq_CXRatgEu3hYfyp3bwrqL6RdgydKKDm0qSdiaqFdT4MF-395f54kuP7U58IvXKpeAjtA0QsQUna8pbHj1TImDjDqnaU3tZYGIkI7ixt4b2Dpd7K4YvwbmPS5v8irmXBrm24-t-wdNUHYlXUTCe0qJCgSFy2B7krqIx1zvRe3aUp49cD6wArAlmP_EeO8OrRjRUOJW96gqGlPpVmwRlopHhPaxneRY-EkmsUfPoUxgTHaBcbBeM_xMDWfsKS5rOheCK5GekIwG