rtual-thread support**\\n\\nI'm noticing that the library supports a virtual-thread dispatcher, but there doesn’t seem to be an environment property associated with it. I need to find evidence in the documentation to clarify this. I should search the migration docs for version 2.0 to see if there’s any mention of the removal of classic typed actors. This may give me the insights I need to understand the changes better. I'll get on this now!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ZjqJAWHgjnS95U8GaIo6ZKFy|fc_0119555cb460abf9016a40b7936a448190bd92f2aaea9f17f9", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "python3 - <<'PY'\nimport urllib.request, re\nurls=[\n 'https://pekko.apache.org/docs/pekko/2.0.0-M1/project/migration-guides.html',\n 'https://pekko.apache.org/docs/pekko/2.0.0-M1/project/migration-guide-1.0.x-2.0.x.html',\n 'https://pekko.apache.org/docs/pekko/2.0.0-M1/migration/migration-guide-1.0.x-2.0.x.html',\n 'https://pekko.apache.org/docs/pekko/2.0.0-M1/release-notes/releases-2.0.html',\n 'https://pekko.apache.org/docs/pekko/2.0.0-M1/project/release-notes.html'\n]\nfor url in urls:\n print('\\n---',url)\n try:\n  data=urllib.request.urlopen(url, timeout=20).read().decode(errors='ignore')\n  print('len',len(data),'title', re.search(r'<title>(.*?)</title>', data, re.S).group(1) if re.search(r'<title>(.*?)</title>',data,re.S) else '')\n  low=data.lower()\n  for term in ['typedactor','typed actor','2.0','removed','pekko-testkit','dependency']:\n   idx=low.find(term.lower())\n   if idx!=-1:\n    print('TERM',term, re.sub(r'\\s+',' ',data[max(0,idx-250):idx+700])[:1000])\n except Exception as e: print('ERR',e)\nPY", "timeout": 60}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 2256, "output": 882, "cacheRead": 30720, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33858, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782626182766, "responseId": "resp_0119555cb460abf9